  "created": "2026-03-16",
  "description": "Negative speed at -0.75, posScatter maximum 1.0, pitchScatter 0.45. Speed is not speed here — it is direction bias. With negative speed every grain plays in reverse AND fires from a random position. The result is a backwards cloud that has no source location: multiple reversed fragments playing simultaneously from unknown origins at slightly different pitches. This is what drowning in a recording sounds like from the inside.",
